27/02/2007
KABUL, Afghanistan -- Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul reaffirmed his country's support for the re-establishment of peace and the stabilisation of Afghanistan, during a visit to Kabul on Monday (February 26th).
Gul met with Afghani counterpart Dadfar Spanta and President Hamid Karzai.
Gul said Ankara is committed to continuing its military engagement in Afghanistan and plans to increase its number of troops in the International Security Assistance Force.
(NTV, TurkishPress.com - 26/02/07)
